pdnCardConfigTable.name: pdnCardConfigTable
pdnCardConfigTable.description: A table that contains information about Mux Forwarding, IP Filtering, IP Scoping and domain name for each VNID.

pdnCardConfigEntry.name: pdnCardConfigEntry
pdnCardConfigEntry.description: A list of configuration information for each VNID.

pdnCardConfigVnidId.name: pdnCardConfigVnidId
pdnCardConfigVnidId.description: The VNID Id number of the virtual network for which this entry contains management information. 'null' is used to create a new entry for MIB browsers which cannot create new entry but can only edit existing entry.

pdnCardConfigDomainName.name: pdnCardConfigDomainName
pdnCardConfigDomainName.description: The Domain name of the ISP for this VNID.

pdnCardConfigMuxFwd.name: pdnCardConfigMuxFwd
pdnCardConfigMuxFwd.description: This object shows if Mux Forwarding has been enabled or disabled by the user.

pdnCardConfigIPFiltering.name: pdnCardConfigIPFiltering
pdnCardConfigIPFiltering.description: This object shows if IP Filtering has been enabled or disabled by the user.

pdnCardConfigIPScoping.name: pdnCardConfigIPScoping
pdnCardConfigIPScoping.description: This object shows if IP Scoping has been enabled or disabled by the user.

pdnCardConfigDbUpdate.name: pdnCardConfigDbUpdate
pdnCardConfigDbUpdate.description: This object is used to control the setting of the objects in this table. When 'nop' is received, no objects are set. When 'update' is received, all objects in this table for which set PDU have been received prior to this set PDU will be set and a new entry will be created if the index does not exist. When 'delete' is received, the entry with the index value will be deleted.
